Privacy Policy
LONG-AWAITED GUESTS LIMITED
understands that your privacy is important to you and that you care about how your information is used and shared online. We respect and value the privacy of everyone who visits Our Site and will only collect and use information in a manner that is beneficial to you and consistent with your rights and Our legal obligations.
This Policy applies to our use of any and all data collected by us in connection with your use of our site. Please read this Privacy Policy carefully and make sure you understand it.
Your acceptance of Our Privacy Policy is deemed to be accepted when you first use our Site AND/OR you will be required to read and accept this Privacy Policy when registering for an Account.
. If you do not accept and agree to this Privacy Policy, you must immediately stop using our site.
Definitions and Interpretations
In this Policy, the following terms have the following meanings:
Account
means an account required to access and/or use certain areas and features of Our Site.
Cookie
means a small text file placed on your computer or device by Our Site when you visit certain areas of Our Site and/or when you use certain features of Our Site.
GDPR
stands for EU General Data Protection Regulation 2016/679 which came into force on 25 January 2022.
User/You/Your/Customer
means the data subject as defined by the GDPR.
Scope - What does this policy cover?
This Privacy Policy applies only to your use of Our site and our application. It does not apply to any websites that are linked from Our Site (regardless of whether we provide those links or share them with other users). We do not control how your data is collected, stored or used by other websites and we encourage you to review the privacy policies of any such websites before providing them with any data.
What data do we collect?
Some data will be collected automatically by our site. Depending on how you use Our Site, we may collect some or all of the following data:
IP address (collected automatically);
web browser type and version (collected automatically);
operating system (assembled automatically);
How do we use your data?
All personal data is securely stored in accordance with the GDPR. We use your information to provide you with the best possible service. It includes:
Providing and managing your Account;
Providing and managing your access to our site;
Personalizing and tailoring your experience on Our Site;
Providing you with Our services;
Personalizing and tailoring Our Services to you;
Responding to messages from you;
Providing you with an email (you can unsubscribe or unsubscribe at any time by clicking the "unsubscribe" button in the email);
Market research;
Analyzing your use of Our Site and collecting feedback
The processing of your personal data is based on Art. 6(1) lit. b GDPR, insofar as this is necessary for the performance of a contract to which the data subject is a party in accordance with the Terms of Use.
With your permission and/or where permitted by law, We may also use your data for marketing purposes, which may include contacting you by email AND/OR telephone with information, news and offers about Our services. However, we will not send you unsolicited marketing or spam and will take all reasonable steps to ensure that your rights are fully protected and that Our obligations under the GDPR and the Privacy and Electronic Communications Regulations (EU Directive) 2003, as amended, are respected. . in 2004, 2011 and 2015.
Advertisers whose content appears on Our Site may engage in so-called "behavioral advertising" - advertising tailored to your preferences based on your activity. Your activity is tracked using cookies. You can control and limit your data used in this way by adjusting your web browser's privacy settings. Please note that We do not control the activities of such advertisers or the information they collect and use. Restricting the use of your data in this way will not remove ads, but will make them less relevant to your interests and activities on Our site.
In accordance with the GDPR, we will ensure that your personal data is processed lawfully, fairly and transparently without prejudice to your rights. We will only process your personal data if at least one of the following grounds applies:
you have given consent to the processing of your personal data for one or more specific purposes;
processing is necessary for the performance of a contract to which you are a party or in order to take steps at the request of you prior to entering into a contract
processing is necessary for compliance with a legal obligation to which we are subject
processing is necessary to protect the vital interests of you or of another natural person;
processing is necessary for the performance of a task carried out in the public interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in the controller;
processing is necessary for the purposes of the legitimate third interests pursued by us or by a party, except where such interests are overridden by the fundamental rights and freedoms of the data subject which require protection of personal data, in particular where the data subject is a child.
How and where do we store your data?
We only keep your data for as long as we need the tools. We have your permission to store them. In any case, We will conduct an annual review to find out if we need to keep your data. Your data will be deleted when we no longer need it in accordance with the terms of our Data Retention Policy.
Your data will only be stored within the European Economic Area (“EEA”) (the EEA includes all EU member states plus Norway). , Iceland and Liechtenstein).
Data security is of great importance to us and in order to protect your data, we have put in place suitable physical, electronic and managerial procedures to protect and protect the data collected through our website.
Despite the security measures We take, it is important to remember that data transmission over the Internet may not be completely secure and that You are advised to take appropriate precautions when transmitting data to Us over the Internet.
We will not sell, buy, provide, trade, or otherwise disclose Account or Transaction data, or personal information about a Cardholder, to anyone other than the Acquirer, Visa/Mastercard corporations, or in response to lawful government requests.
What happens if our business changes hands?
We may expand or contract Our business from time to time, which may include the sale and/or transfer of control of all or part of Our business. Data provided by users will, if relevant to any part of Our business so transferred, be transferred with that part and the new owner or new controlling party, subject to the terms of this Privacy Policy, will be permitted to use the data for the purposes for which it was originally assembled by us.
In the event that any of your data is transferred in this way, you will not be contacted in advance and notified of the changes.
How can you control your data?
When you submit information through Our Site, you may be given the option to restrict our use of your data. We are committed to providing you with strict control over our use of your data (including the ability to opt out of receiving emails from us, which you can do by unsubscribing using the links provided in our emails and managing your account. Your right not to
disclose information and your right to withdraw information once you have
provided it. You may be able to access certain areas of our site without providing any data at all. However, in order to use all the features and functionality available on our site, you may be required to submit or allow the collection of certain
data. You can restrict the use of cookies in your internet browser.
You may withdraw your consent to our use of your personal information at any time by contacting us using the information provided in the section and we will delete your information from our systems. However, you acknowledge that this may limit our ability to provide you with the best possible service.
How can you access your data?
You have the legal right to request a copy of any of your personal data held by Us (where such data is stored). Please contact us for more information at support@medicalgermanp.app. Alternatively, please refer to our Data Protection Policy.
What cookies do we use and why?
Our Site may place and access certain essential cookies on your computer or device. First party cookies are placed directly by us and used only by us. We use cookies to facilitate and improve your experience of using our site and to provide and improve our services. We have carefully selected these cookies and have taken steps to ensure that your privacy is protected and respected at all times.
By using Our Site, you may also receive certain third-party cookies on your computer or device. Third party cookies are placed by websites, services and/or parties other than us. We use third party cookies on our website. These cookies are not an integral part of the operation of Our Site.
All cookies used by and on Our Site are used in accordance with applicable UK and EU cookie law.
Before any cookies are placed on your computer or device, you will be shown a pop-up window asking for your consent to set these cookies. By giving your consent to the placement of cookies, you allow Us to provide you with the best experience and services. You can, if you wish, refuse consent to the placement of cookies; however, some features of Our Site may not work fully or as intended. You will be given the option to allow only essential cookies and block third-party cookies.
Some of the features of Our site depend on cookies. EU Cookie Law considers these cookies to be "strictly necessary". Your consent will not be asked for the placement of these cookies. You can still block these cookies by changing your internet browser settings, but please be aware that our site may not work as intended if you do so. We have made sure that your privacy is not at risk by allowing them.
Our Site uses analytics services provided by third parties. Website Analytics refers to a set of tools used to collect and analyze usage statistics that allow Us to better understand how people use Our Site. This, in turn, allows Us to improve Our Site and the services offered through it. You do not have to allow Us to use these cookies as described below, however, while their use does not pose any risk to your privacy or your secure use of Our Site, it allows Us to continually improve Our Site, making it better and better. useful experience for you. You can delete these cookies and prevent future use by following the steps below.
You can view all the cookies we use, enable or disable cookies, and change or withdraw your consent on our cookie statement page or in your internet browser. Most internet browsers also allow you to choose whether you want to disable all cookies or only third-party cookies. By default, most internet browsers accept cookies, but this can be changed. For more information, refer to the help menu in your Internet browser or the documentation that came with your device.
You can delete cookies at any time, however you may lose any information that allows you to access our site more quickly and efficiently, including but not limited to login and personalization options.
It is recommended that you keep your Internet browser and operating system up to date and consult the help and guidance provided by your Internet browser developer and the manufacturer of your computer or device if you are unsure of your privacy settings.
Summary of your rights under the GDPR Under the GDPR, you have:
the right to request access to, deletion or correction of your personal data held by us;
the right to file a complaint with a supervisory authority;
receive information about what data processing is taking place;
the right to restrict processing;
the right to data portability;
object to the processing of your personal data;
rights regarding automated decision-making and profiling To enforce any of the above rights, or if you have any other questions about Our Site or this Privacy Policy, please contact Us. You can find more information about your rights under the GDPR in GDPR articles: 15, 16, 17, 18, 20, 21, 77. 1
Automated decision-making and profiling
We do not use personal data for automated decision-making purposes and these decisions have a legal (or similarly significant effect) on you.
Data Protection Officer
If you have any questions about our Site or this Privacy Policy, please contact our Data Protection Officer at support@medicalgerman.app. Please make sure that your request is understandable, especially if it is a request for information about your data that we hold.
Changes to our Privacy Policy
We may change this Privacy Policy as we deem necessary from time to time or as required by law. Any changes will be posted on Our Site immediately and you will be deemed to have accepted the terms of the Privacy Policy the first time you use Our Site following the change. We encourage you to check this page regularly for the latest developments.